From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 12:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] mqtt: arm TCP keepalive on the broker socket

obuspa relies entirely on libmosquitto's application-layer PINGREQ
timer (Device.MQTT.Client.{i}.KeepAliveTime) to detect a broken MQTT
session. When the WAN address is briefly removed and re-added (e.g.
DHCP renewal in CDRouter prplos.1.2.9 on OSPv2), the TCP socket can
remain ESTABLISHED in the kernel while no traffic flows end-to-end.
PINGREQ writes succeed into the kernel buffer, libmosquitto thinks
the ping was sent, and obuspa never notices the dead peer.

Arm SO_KEEPALIVE with tight probe values (idle=10, intvl=5, cnt=3)
on the libmosquitto-owned socket immediately after each successful
mosquitto_connect_bind_v5() / mosquitto_connect(). The kernel then
reports the dead peer within ~25 s; the resulting socket error
surfaces through mosquitto_loop_read/write and triggers a reconnect
via the existing HandleMqttError path.

libmosquitto creates a fresh fd on every connect, so the setsockopt
must be re-applied here. setsockopt failures are logged at warning
level but do not abort the connection.

Fixes: PPW-1837
Assisted-by: claude:opus-4-7:1m-context
Signed-off-by: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
---
 src/core/mqtt.c | 32 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 32 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/core/mqtt.c b/src/core/mqtt.c
--- a/src/core/mqtt.c
+++ b/src/core/mqtt.c
@@ -49,6 +49,7 @@
 #include <errno.h>
 #include <math.h>
 #include <fcntl.h>
+#include <netinet/tcp.h>
 #include <openssl/ssl.h>
 #include <openssl/bio.h>
 #include <openssl/err.h>
@@ -2647,6 +2648,37 @@ int Connect(mqtt_client_t *client)
         goto exit;
     }

+    // Arm TCP keepalive on the libmosquitto-owned socket so the kernel
+    // detects a silently half-dead peer (e.g. after a WAN DHCP renewal
+    // that leaves the socket in ESTABLISHED with no traffic) within
+    // ~ TCP_KEEPIDLE + TCP_KEEPCNT * TCP_KEEPINTVL seconds. The error
+    // surfaces through mosquitto_loop_read/write and triggers reconnect
+    // via the existing HandleMqttError path. libmosquitto creates a new
+    // fd on every connect, so this must be re-applied here. Failures
+    // are non-fatal.
+    {
+        int sock = mosquitto_socket(client->mosq);
+        if (sock != -1)
+        {
+            int on = 1;
+            int idle = 10;
+            int intvl = 5;
+            int cnt = 3;
+
+            if (setsockopt(sock, SOL_SOCKET,  SO_KEEPALIVE,  &on,    sizeof(on))    != 0)
+                USP_LOG_Warning("%s: setsockopt(SO_KEEPALIVE) failed: %s",  __FUNCTION__, strerror(errno));
+
+            if (setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_TCP, TCP_KEEPIDLE,  &idle,  sizeof(idle))  != 0)
+                USP_LOG_Warning("%s: setsockopt(TCP_KEEPIDLE) failed: %s",  __FUNCTION__, strerror(errno));
+
+            if (setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_TCP, TCP_KEEPINTVL, &intvl, sizeof(intvl)) != 0)
+                USP_LOG_Warning("%s: setsockopt(TCP_KEEPINTVL) failed: %s", __FUNCTION__, strerror(errno));
+
+            if (setsockopt(sock, IPPROTO_TCP, TCP_KEEPCNT,   &cnt,   sizeof(cnt))   != 0)
+                USP_LOG_Warning("%s: setsockopt(TCP_KEEPCNT) failed: %s",   __FUNCTION__, strerror(errno));
+        }
+    }
+
 exit:
     // Free the connect properties (MQTTv5 only)
     if (proplist != NULL)
